  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A monkey fever patient is diagnosed in Japan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The first case of monkey flu has been reported from Japan. The patient was reported as Japan was preparing for the virus after the World Health Organization declared it a global public health emergency over the weekend.",
        "The patient is a 30-year-old resident of Tokyo. In late June, he traveled to Europe, and on his return to Japan in mid-July, an associate tested positive for monkey flu.",
        "The patient is currently being treated at a hospital in Tokyo and is in a stable condition. Acute itching, fever, headache, swollen lymph nodes and muscle aches are symptoms of monkeypox."
      ],
